# =============================================================================
# kwin_lib/window.py
# Generated by: Claude Sonnet 4.6
#
# Window mutation operations — all implemented as KWin JS scripts that call
# back to Python via callDBus().
#
# Key design notes from testing:
#   • frameGeometry position (x, y) can be set; size is ignored by Wayland
#     apps (the compositor cannot force a client to resize)
#   • Screen assignment uses workspace.sendClientToScreen(window, output);
#     the output object is found by iterating workspace.screens by name.
#     Note: __w.output.name does NOT update within the same script execution
#     after sendClientToScreen() -- fire-and-trust, same as tile().
#   • Desktop assignment uses w.desktops = [desktopObject]
#   • w.output is read-only; sendToOutput() does not exist in this KWin
#   • Qt.rect() is not available in the scripting sandbox
#   • setMaximize(h, v), minimized, activeWindow all work as expected
#   • Spin-wait loops (Date.now()) are used for intra-script delays because
#     KWin's JS sandbox has no async/await or setTimeout
#
# Result shape convention:
#   Every JS send() call returns at minimum:
#     { ok: bool, op: string }
#   Plus op-specific fields as documented per method.
#   elapsed_ms is injected by ScriptRunner.run() on the Python side.
#
# Verbose mode:
#   Construct WindowManager with verbose=True to print a debug line after
#   every KWin script call showing the op name, result dict, and timing.
